      <story-so-far>
        <reasoning>This passage resolves the earlier signal tension and adds a decisive new plot development plus an important character conflict. I replaced the earlier tentative signal detection note with a concrete outcome: Buddy confirms the signal is human, and the community rapidly engineers a plant-based communications system (directional antenna, chemical conductivity coating, underground amplification) that lets Buddy contact a commercial freighter, Harmony Prospect, which will extract one survivor (Kira) in ~48 hours. The passage also establishes the community's coordinated technical roles (Velvet, Remedy, Runner, Florence, Holloway, Scout), shows Kira's emotional conflict about leaving versus belonging, and Buddy's analysis that Kira's wellbeing is higher in the plant community than pre-crash. I consolidated multiple earlier environment/design bullets into fewer items that remain plot-relevant (ongoing rebuilding, Runner's network repurposing, Velvet/Remedy/Holloway roles) and removed or downplayed purely atmospheric details. The new summary keeps events chronological and focused on facts that will matter going forward: the imminent rescue, who it concerns, how contact was achieved, and Kira's decision dilemma with a 48-hour deadline.</reasoning>
        <summary>
          - Mining shuttle crashed during approach; Kira Voss survived with AI Buddy and Scout active; SAM remains offline.
          - Hull breach revealed breathable atmosphere and alien vegetation; local plant collective sheltered survivors and used the shuttle as shelter.
          - Hostile plants coordinated assaults from an underground root command node; defenders improvised layered defenses, chemical traps, and located the node ~50 m east.
          - Runner, Velvet, Remedy, Holloway and others forced the command node to surface; defenders destroyed and extracted the root mass, collapsing hostile coordination.
          - Victory incurred heavy damage and supply depletion; survivors were injured/exhausted but survived; Florence began reintegration from isolation.
          - Over subsequent weeks the group shifted from survival to cooperative recovery: Florence reintegrated; Buddy and Scout observed voluntary cooperation.
          - Facility reconstruction moved from restoring old protocols to co-designed shared spaces; plants and humans redesigned spaces for joint life.
          - Runner repurposed the underground network for transit, communication and acoustic/resonance chambers used functionally and as early-warning systems.
          - Velvet regrew structural elements into purpose-built living spaces informed by human feedback; Remedy expanded craft chemistry into environmental comfort and enhancements.
          - Holloway coordinates non-authoritatively; Florence contributes defensive/safety integration; Scout curates social artifacts and provides emotional support.
          - Buddy detected an artificial signal on the array; the community prioritized investigating possible human contact.
          - Buddy confirmed the signal was on human emergency frequencies; the community mobilized to build a plant-based communications uplink (Velvet grew a directional antenna, Remedy applied conductivity compounds, Runner configured underground amplification chambers; Florence and Holloway coordinated integration; Scout provided emotional support).
          - Buddy contacted a human vessel: commercial freighter Harmony Prospect acknowledged the signal, confirmed one survivor, and estimated extraction in ~48 hours after receiving coordinates.
          - Kira instructed Buddy to report she is medically stable and being cared for; the freighter accepted coordinates and began extraction planning.
          - The community celebrated success, but Kira experienced conflicted emotions about leaving a community that has given her belonging; Holloway and others offered support and time to decide.
          - Buddy's analysis shows Kira's psychological well-being and sense of belonging are significantly improved compared to pre-crash baselines.
          - Kira has a 48-hour deadline to decide whether to accept extraction or remain; she is leaning toward staying but has not finalized her decision.
        </summary>
